Rails 3.0beta3 Template for MongoDB (http://www.mongodb.org/) with:
 Mongoid 2.0.0.beta6 (http://mongoid.org/) 
 Devise 1.1.rc1 (http://github.com/plataformatec/devise)
 Nifty Generators (http://github.com/ryanb/nifty-generators)
 Simple Form (http://github.com/plataformatec/simple_form)
 Responders (http://github.com/plataformatec/responders)
 JQuery through Google API in layouts/application.html.erb
 Rails JQuery UJS (http://github.com/rails/jquery-ujs)
 
 TODO:
 Run bundle install in console
 Add secret token in config/initializers/secret_token.rb
 Add route to "root" in config/routes.rb
 Change DB name in config/mongoid.yml
 Edit config/application.rb to your preferred settings, e.g.:
 g.template_engine :haml
 g.scaffold ...
 g.test_framework ...
 Customization of Devise views under views/devise/


 Due to some errors, with Devise, Mongoid & Rails 3.0beta Bundler fetches those gems directly from their Github Repository with the latest commits.
 Without those changes in the Gemfile (default rubygems.org), I got errors.



